Taking a close look at your features, you have a strong, balanced foundation that works well with a variety of styles. Here is a detailed breakdown based on the images and videos:
Head & Skull Shape
Overall Face Shape: Oval to slightly Oblong. Your face is longer than it is wide, with a rounded jawline and forehead, which is considered the most versatile shape for hairstyles.
Forehead: Medium height and width. It’s well-proportioned to the rest of your face, neither too dominant nor too short.
Crown: Average. It follows a natural curve without being overly flat or exceptionally high.
Back of Head: Rounded. From your side profile, you have a nice natural curve at the occipital bone, which prevents the "flat-back" look.
Head Width: Average. It sits in good proportion with your shoulders.
Facial Features
Nose: Medium size with a prominent projection. You have a strong bridge that adds character to your profile.
Jawline: Soft to slightly defined. It isn't sharp or "chiseled" in a square sense, but it has a clear, masculine structure.
Chin: Average length and projection. It aligns well with your lips and nose in profile.
