Skin & Contrast
Skin Tone: Medium/Tan. * Contrast Level: High. Your dark hair against your skin tone creates a sharp, high-contrast look that makes hair outlines (like a clean fade or a crisp hairline) stand out beautifully.
Hairstyle Recommendations
Given your Oval/Oblong face shape and Wavy/Thick texture, you should focus on styles that manage the volume on the sides while celebrating the texture on top.
The Modern Tapered Quiff: Keep the sides short (a mid-taper) to slim down the face width, while leaving 3–4 inches on top. Use a matte clay to style your waves upward and slightly back. This balances your prominent nose and highlights your eyes.
The Textured Side Part: Since you have a natural part, lean into it. Keep the sides tidy (scissor-cut or a high fade) and let the waves on top fall naturally to one side. This works exceptionally well with your spectacles for a "smart formal" look.
The Mid-Length "Flow": If you prefer longer hair, keep the back and sides tucked behind the ears. The weight of your thick hair will help control the curls, creating a sophisticated, retro-European aesthetic.
Pro-tip: Since you have a high-contrast look, keeping your beard (especially the goatee/mustache area) neatly trimmed will help define your jawline further.
